Defendant Richard C Helper in court, in custody, with attorney Katie B. Bricco.   Timothy F. Westphal appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Plea Colloquy.
  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 2.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count 1 is dismissed.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

9 months Jail (Credit - 116 days) 

Term of Probation: 12 months

Conditions of Probation:
- Mental Health Evaluation and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Referred to department vocational rehabiliation;
- Referred to Day Report Center for 6 months (can start at anytime);
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Obtain a valid license within first 6 months subject to mental health evaluation and approval of the agent;
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment when able - in lieu of employment the court orders 20 hours of community service each week of probation;
- No contact with vicitim or her address.


Costs: $253.00 
DNA Surcharge:  $200.00
DNA Sample Waived.
(To be paid as a condition of probation by the end of probation and/or 46 hours of community service to be completed by completion of probation.  Court must receive notice of completion prior to due date.)
